Report: act_report¶

Insights:¶

Given below are the insights gained from analysing the wrangled datasets.

  1. There is a very strong positive correlation between favorites and retweets. It was found while analyzing the datasets, that a very strong positive correlation exists between favorites and retweets. The relationship here does not outrightly conclude absolute dependency of favorite counts and retweet counts, it is only for analyses. Further examination is recommended before any conclusion can be drawn. The visualization is as given below:

  1. Ratings around 12 have the highest distribution. While the analysis was done to check how distributed the dog ratings were, it was found, from the data frame used, that the ratings with rating_numerators around 12 have the highest distribution. The visualization can be found below;

The histogram shows how distributed the rating scores were.

  1. Scottish Deerhound has the lowest mean favorite rating, while Bedlington_Terrier has the highest mean favorite ratings

Analysis to find the mean favorite ratings was done and it was found that Scottish Deerhound has the lowest mean favorite rating, while Bedlington_Terrier has the highest mean favorite rating. Being quite curious, the images of these dog breeds were visualized, and here is what was found from the given image URL in the dataset.

  • #### Scottish Deerhound with the lowet mean favorite rating

  • #### Bedlington_Terrier - with the highest mean favorite rating

The aim of these analyses is not to show the best or worst dog breed. This is just for the sake of project assignments. Further research, examination, analysis, and documentation are recommended before drawing any conclusion.
